sneakers.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Bordeaux'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Bordeaux’ takes on a familiar color scheme tied to the shoe’s successor, the Air Jordan 7. Soft nubuck construction is utilized on the upper, featuring a neutral grey base with contrasting black overlays. The translucent tongue features a multicolor print that replicates the look of the AJ7’s neoprene tongue, while Bordeaux accents land on the throat and molded heel tab. Lightweight cushioning arrives via the visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of a grey and black polyurethane midsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 1 Low OG Shattered Backboard
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 1 Low OG ‘Starfish’ features a familiar color combination that recalls the brand’s ‘Shattered Backboard’ series. The low-top carries an all-leather upper that pairs a crisp white base with contrasting orange overlays at the forefoot, heel and eyestay. Contrasting black hits land on the Swoosh, laces and Jordan Wings logo stamped on the heel tab. Nike Air branding decorates the sockliner and woven tongue tag. The sneaker is mounted on a rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air sole cushioning in the heel.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Oreo' 2021
sneakers.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Oreo’ 2021brings back a simple two-tone colorway first released in 2013. The build is faithful to the original, featuring a black suede upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a grey Jumpman embroidered on the tongue. Contrasting white hits appear on the collar lining, interior tongue and Jumpman heel branding. The mid-top sits on a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air unit nestled in the heel and black shark-tooth detailing dusted in white speckles. Underfoot, an icy rubber outsole delivers stop-and-go traction.

sneakers.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Light'
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Light’ updates the minimalist sneaker with UV-sensitive technology, a first for Kanye West’s lifestyle imprint. Under artificial light, the Primeknit upper projects a subtle ivory finish. Exposure to direct sunlight yields soft pink coloring throughout the knit build, while the monofilament side stripe darkens to an amber hue. The color-shifting assembly is supported by a standard rubber-wrapped Boost midsole.

sneakers.name: New Balance RC 1300 Kith 10th Anniversary Elephant Skin Grey
sneakers.story: The Ronnie Fieg x New Balance RC 1300 ‘Elephant Skin’ is taken from a three-piece pack celebrating Kith’s 10th anniversary. The collaborative effort, inspired by Fieg’s very first project with New Balance, features a light grey mesh upper with tonal suede overlays and a leather ‘N’ logo covered in Kith’s debossed monogram print. Atop the lateral forefoot, ‘NB’ branding is embroidered on the right shoe, while Kith’s Pegasus graphic adorns the left. Those flourishes are joined by a dual-branded tongue tag and mismatched leather heel tabs debossed with ‘Kith’ and ‘Fieg’ wordmarks. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of an ENCAP Reveal midsole, supported underfoot by a durable Vibram outsole.

sneakers.name: New Balance RC 1300 Kith 10th Anniversary White Pepper
sneakers.story: Dropping as part of a three-piece pack celebrating the 10th anniversary of Kith, the Ronnie Fieg x New Balance RC 1300 ‘White Pepper’ applies a subdued tan finish to a traditional mesh and suede build. The sneaker is accented with a number of unique branding elements, including Kith’s debossed monogram print on the signature ‘N’ logo; mismatched leather heel tabs with debossed ‘Kith’ and ‘Fieg’ wordmarks; and embroidered NB and Pegasus graphics on the lateral forefoot of the right and left shoe, respectively. The lifestyle runner sits atop an ENCAP Reveal midsole, which is reinforced by a green rubber Vibram outsole.

sneakers.name: New Balance RC 1300 Kith 10th Anniversary Antler
sneakers.story: Taken from a 10th anniversary pack recognizing Kith’s decade in business, the Ronnie Fieg x New Balance RC 1300 ‘Antler’ dresses the lifestyle runner in mauve-colored mesh and pigskin suede. Kith’s monogram print is debossed on the signature ‘N’ logo, while the lateral forefoot features an embroidered ‘NB’ and Pegasus graphic on the left and right shoe, respectively. ‘Kith’ and ‘Fieg’ are debossed on mismatched leather heel tabs. Lightweight cushioning is provided by ENCAP Reveal midsole, supported underfoot by a light grey Vibram outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Blue Tint
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Blue Tint’ applies an especially vibrant hue to the lightweight polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and enlivened with reflective accents, including oversized 700 branding on the lateral side panel. Contrasting black hits make their way to the collar lining, tongue and reinforced no-sew overlays at the toe and heel. The seamless build rides on a sculpted black polyurethane midsole, enhanced with full-length drop-in Boost cushioning.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air NFH 'Multi'
sneakers.story: The Jordan Air NFH ‘Multi’ delivers a color-blocked lifestyle silhouette infused with basketball DNA. Contrasting blue and green mesh paneling is utilized on the upper, with black nubuck overlays accentuating the shoe’s retro-inspired look. An orange webbing pull tab at the heel provides an unexpected pop of color. The multicolor assemblage up top is offset by a white sculpted foam midsole, fitted with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a modified herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Dark Slate’ delivers a blacked-out iteration of Kanye West’s boundary-pushing silhouette. Stripped of color and exterior branding, the knit upper is secured with an integrated lacing system and topped with an elastic, sock-like cuff. In lieu of a traditional midsole, the rubber outsole sprouts tapered appendages that wrap up the heel and side panels of the deconstructed build, providing support and enhanced durability within its grasp.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Cinder
sneakers.story: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole. This shoe released exclusively on Yeezy Supply.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Enflame Orange’ updates the minimalist slip-on with a deep citrus hue. The lightweight build, formed with injected EVA, features breathable open-toe construction and a plush footbed for soft landings. The latter is marked with adidas’ three-stripe logo, representing the only bit of exterior branding. Pronounced flex grooves distinguish the outsole, offering improved cushioning and durable traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Mist
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Mist’ is taken from the four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, which introduces a refreshed take on the flagship Yeezy sneaker. Traditional Primeknit is replaced by a monofilament mesh upper, finished in a dark beige hue and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. The sock-like one-piece upper is reinforced with an internal cage and equipped with a webbing heel tab for easy on and off. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added support and durability, provides responsive cushioning. This shoe released exclusively in Europe, Africa, India, the Middle East, Russia, Ukraine, and China.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Ice’ represents one of four monochromatic colorways that collectively introduce a refreshed take on the minimalist silhouette. In lieu of traditional Primeknit, the upper is constructed from monofilament mesh, rendered in an icy blue shade and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. Additional details include an interior cage, webbing heel tab and molded eyelets. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning. This shoe released exclusively in in North America, Latin America and China.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Clay
sneakers.story: Dropping alongside three companion colorways in a similar one-note finish, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Clay’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an upper constructed from monofilament mesh. The lightweight material is rendered in a pale coral hue and reinforced with an internal cage. A webbing pull tab is affixed to the heel, lining up with tonal stripe detailing on the lateral side. The sneaker rides on a standard full-length Boost midsole with rubber-wrapped sidewalls. This shoe released exclusively in the Asia Pacific and China.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Enflame Amber
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Enflame Amber’ features muted earth tones on the upper, constructed from breathable beige mesh with dark brown suede overlays throughout the midfoot. A tonal beige toe cap reinforces an unexpected pop of blue mesh on the toe box. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a coral-hued EVA carrier and made visible through cut-out detailing on the herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Bright Cyan’ makes use of a lightweight polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and finished in a vibrant aqua hue. No-sew overlays provide lightweight durability and support, while reflective detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker’s signature ‘700’ branding adorns the lateral side. Responsive cushioning arrives via sculpted PU midsole, housing full-length Boost cushioning within and reinforced with a herringbone-tread outsole underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Taupe Light
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Taupe Light’ steps out in an understated monochromatic colorway that allows the sneaker’s premium construction to come to the fore. Open mesh makes up the majority of the upper, fortified with cow suede and leather overlays throughout. Reflective piping around the eyelets provides a hi-vis element, while a rubber midfoot wrap offers enhanced durability. The layered build is supported by an adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe, the adidas KB8 3.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Alien Blue
sneakers.colorway: Alien Blue RF/Alien Blue RF/Alien Blue RF
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Alien Blue’ delivers a wintry colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, highlighted by a grey and cream Primeknit upper with reflective detailing for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A subtle green finish distinguishes the monofilament window that adds textural depth to the sneaker’s lateral side panel. The sock-like build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent blue rubber cage and supported by a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner 'Mineral Blue' coats the hybrid silhouette in a monochromatic finish. The slip-on blends elements of sneakers and sandals, arriving in soft yet durable foam. A series of large and small ventilation ports enhance airflow, with branding limited to a discreet adidas logo underfoot.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 35 Low 'White Black'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 35 Low ‘White Black’ treats the lightweight hoops shoe to an essential two-tone makeover. The black textile upper is fortified with contrasting white leather overlays and equipped with a low-cut collar for improved ankle mobility. Subtle pops of Varsity Red appear on a ‘23’ stamped on the lateral forefoot and a woven Nike tag stitched onto the back heel. On the lateral side, supportive Flightwire cables radiate out from the Eclipse Plate 2.0, featuring a hollowed-out core that reveals Zoom Air units in the forefoot and heel.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Flash Orange
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange' carries a breathable jacquard mesh upper with wavy overlays in contrasting black and burnt orange accents. The mid-top is equipped with a stretchy neoprene collar and fortified with a synthetic suede toe cap. A seamless heel counter extends to the midsole, packed with full-length Boost cushioning wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a classic herringbone tread for stop-and-go traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Sumac
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Sumac’ treats the bulky silhouette to a unique palette made up of rich earth tones and sharply contrasting primary colors. The upper is constructed from brown mesh with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. They’re joined by midfoot suede overlays in blue and indigo, along with bold a crimson overlay that wraps around the collar and snakes underneath the stitched-on eyelets. The sneaker is mounted on a podular adiPRENE+ that offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Tactile Orange
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Tactical Orange’ makes use of a ventilated brown mesh upper with contrasting suede overlays in varying shades of blue. A padded high-cut collar combines with a plush tongue to deliver a snug, comfortable fit, while a brown rubber mudguard offers lightweight support and abrasion-resistant durability. The bulky silhouette rests on a podular adiPRENE+ midsole, modeled after the adidas KB8 3 and finished in a subtle orange hue.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Enflame
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Enflame’ spotlights the sneaker’s adiPRENE+ tooling with a vibrant orange finish. Offering a blend of impact absorption and responsive cushioning, the podular midsole is directly inspired by the adidas KB8 3, released in 1999 as Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe. Up top, the sneaker’s complex build combines brown open mesh with soft suede overlays in tan, grey and indigo. A rubber midfoot wrap provides added durability and support.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Pure
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Pure’ highlights a one-note beige finish throughout the exterior of the slip-on. Lightweight and durable, injected EVA foam makes up the composition of the one-piece build. The minimalist design is marked with an embossed adidas logo on the soft top layer of the footbed, good for immediate step-in comfort. Underfoot, the outsole is configured with deep flex grooves for a smooth ride and optimal grip.

sneakers.name: Yeezy Slides 'Core' 2021
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Core’ showcases a monochromatic light brown hue throughout the exterior of the futuristic sandal, featuring open-toe construction on a cushy EVA foam build. Branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo stamped on the footbed and a Yeezy wordmark on the lining of the upper. Underfoot, the outsole is treated to a series of deep horizontal grooves for soft cushioning and enhanced traction.

sneakers.name: Yeezy Slides 'Resin' 2021
sneakers.story: The 2021 edition of the adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Resin’ treats Kanye West’s futuristic sandal to a neutral finish in keeping with the established Yeezy aesthetic. The pillowy slip-on is built with injected EVA foam, complete with a soft top layer across the footbed for immediate step-in comfort. Underfoot, deep horizontal grooves are carved into the serrated outsole, good for a blend of impact protection and enhanced traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Bright Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Bright Blue’ uses sharply contrasting finishes to delineate the lifestyle runner’s upper and tooling. The latter pairs sculpted orange sidewalls with a contrasting black rubber outsole, featuring a herringbone traction pattern with cut-out detailing that reveals a drop-in Boost midsole. Up top, royal blue mesh is reinforced with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel, along with black suede midfoot panels enlivened with reflective detailing.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Frosted Blue’ showcases a contrasting two-tone color palette on a retro-inspired lifestyle sneaker that traces a lineage to the adidas KB8 III. The upper is composed of stretchy elastane in a vibrant blue finish, fortified with suede overlays in a lighter blue shade. They’re joined by tan suede on the sneaker’s segmented eyestay and reinforced toe wrap. Additional details include toggle lacing and a padded, high-cut collar. Cushioning arrives via a podular adiPRENE midsole that gives the nod to adidas’ Feet You Wear technology.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Taupe Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot “Taupe Blue” is a military inspired all-season boot made in collaboration by Kanye West and adidas. Combining high fashion and rugged workwear aesthetics, the Yeezy Desert Boot features design intricacies from a popular model in the series, the Yeezy 500. The suede toe and leather overlays that appear on the 500 silhouette also grace the Desert Boot. Specifically, the “Taupe Blue’s” upper features an earthy brown mesh base with tan and beige overlaid panels. Adidas paints the chunky midsole in an attention-grabbing Taupe Blue hue. Underfoot, the ridged outsole provides the wearer with optimal traction on various surfaces. Release date: March 29, 2021.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sand
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Sand’ delivers a monotone iteration of Kanye West’s clog-like silhouette. Featuring a slightly darker tan shade than the debut ‘Ararat’ colorway from 2020, the slip-on makes use of a flexible one-piece build that combines standard EVA with an algae-based foam compound. Multiple ventilation ports allow feet to breathe, while textured interiors offer no-slip grip. Underfoot, a classic herringbone tread provides dependable traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MXT Moon Gray
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘MXT Moon Grey’ showcases a neutral two-tone color scheme on the sculpted, futuristic slip-on. Ventilation ports are riddled throughout the pliable one-piece build, constructed from a sustainable blend of EVA and an algae-based foam. A textured interior provides no-slip comfort, while the outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for reliable grip. Exterior branding is limited to a discreet adidas wordmark underneath the heel.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kyanite
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Kyanite’ showcases flowing stripes of blue coloring throughout the breathable upper, constructed from monofilament engineered mesh with exoskeletal RPU overlays coated in a glow-in-the-dark finish. Interior bootie construction delivers a snug fit, while a reinforced rubber toe cap provides added durability. The sneaker rides on a lightweight EVA midsole encapsulated in an off-white PU cage, supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Ash Pearl’ applies contrast color blocking to the re-engineered Primeknit upper. Most of the knit build features a blend of indigo, grey and navy fibers, while the top half of the sneaker’s lateral side is rendered in subtle cream and beige tones. The latter hue is repeated on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. The lightweight sneaker is supported by a full-length Boost midsole, its sidewalls reinforced with an off-white rubber cage.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Sea Teal
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Sea Teal’ dresses the lifestyle silhouette in a breathable knit upper that blends mostly neutral grey and black tones with washed-out teal accents. A soft elastic collar provides a comfortable fit around the ankle, while the seamless heel counter is designed to hug the back of the foot for enhanced containment. A semi-translucent rubber cage shores up the full-length Boost midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Covellite’ showcases a mix of navy, indigo, and grey tones throughout the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The camo-like design is punctuated by perforated detailing that accompanies the sneaker’s semi-translucent monofilament window, woven into the side panel to enhance the breathability of the sock-like build. Responsive cushioning arrives via a caged full-length Boost midsole, featuring a stacked, elevated heel and supported underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Cream
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 ‘Cream’ delivers an unassuming colorway of Kanye West’s running-inspired silhouette. The upper features rolled knit construction in a pale grey hue, reinforced with tonal no-sew skins and tan nubuck overlays. An off-white finish distinguishes the exaggerated EVA midsole, featuring sculpted sidewalls that conceal a full-length drop-in Boost unit. Underfoot, the rubber outsole uses a classic herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White
sneakers.story: The Yeezy 450 ‘Cloud White’ highlights neutral hues on a deconstructed sneaker developed with a design assist from Steve Smith, the mastermind behind iconic silhouettes ranging from the New Balance 997 to the Reebok Instapump Fury. Exterior branding is stripped from the one-piece knit textile upper, secured with an elastic cuff and an integrated lacing system. The minimalist design is encroached upon by the unique configuration of the molded outsole, featuring a set of ‘fingers’ that wrap up the side panels.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Stone
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Ash Stone’ highlights subdued earth tones throughout its re-engineered Primeknit upper. The complementary blend of tan, brown and grey fibers is arranged in different weaves that create an intricate, patchwork-like design, offset by a coral-colored side stripe on the sneaker’s lateral side. The sock-like build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added durability and support. This colorway launched exclusively in Europe, Russia, Ukraine and the Asia-Pacific region.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Ash Blue’ carries a re-engineered Primeknit upper constructed from a blend of slate blue, grey and black fibers. A pale yellow hue distinguishes the post-dyed monofilament side stripe woven into the sneaker’s lateral side panel, delivering added breathability and an unexpected pop of color. The sock-like upper rides on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped up in a semi-translucent rubber cage for improved stability and durability.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Shale Warm
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Wakaran’ showcases neutral beige tones on a flexible elastane upper, equipped with a comfortable padded collar and reinforced with suede and leather overlays. Reflective piping delivers added visibility in low-light conditions. Progressively darker shades of grey distinguish the podular adiPRENE+ midsole and rubber outsole, featuring a wavy traction pattern for optimal grip. The exterior is stripped of distinguishing logos and trademarks, relegating the sneaker’s branding elements to the sockliner instead.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Mist Slate
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Mist’ delivers an understated colorway of the retro-inspired silhouette that borrows tooling from Kobe Bryant’s KB8 3, itself modeled after the brand’s Feet You Wear cushioning technology. Up top, grey elastane is fortified with tonal suede and leather overlays that reveal a subtle greenish cast. Reflective piping traces the wavy lines of the mudguard, while a grey rubber wrap provides added durability. A matching grey adiPRENE+ midsole delivers impact absorption and a smooth ride.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Sun
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Sun’ treats the lifestyle runner to a lively color scheme that accentuates the silhouette’s multi-layered build. The majority of the mesh and leather upper is rendered in varying shades of yellow, contrasted by a black suede overlay that extends to mesh forefoot panels in blue and teal. A clashing coral finish is applied to the bulky midsole, featuring full-length drop-in Boost cushioning for a smooth ride. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole delivers optimal grip.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Yecoraite Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Yecoraite’ carries a flexible Primeknit upper embellished with a camo-like pattern made up of neutral grey and off-white fibers. The minimalist sock-like build is accented with decorative laces and a translucent monofilament window in a pale orange hue. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent rubber for improved stability and durability. A subtle coral finish is applied to the herringbone rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 35 'Bred'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 35 ‘Bred’ takes on an iconic color scheme that’s virtually synonymous with the Jordan franchise at large. A mostly black finish is executed on the upper, featuring a blend of suede, mesh and grid-like netting that recalls the Air Jordan 5. Flecks of red can be seen on the Flightwire cables that radiate out from the sneaker’s side panels. Additional pops of Fire Red land on the Jumpman logo on the silver reflective tongue — another carryover from the AJ5 — and Eclipse Plate, supported by a matching herringbone outsole.

sneakers.name: New Balance 992 Kith Kithmas Burgundy White
sneakers.story: Releasing as part of the three-piece ‘Kithmas Collection,’ the Kith x New Balance 992 ‘Burgundy Reef’ dresses the lifestyle runner in sharply contrasting hues. The upper makes use of a breathable white mesh base, fortified with burgundy pigskin suede on the mudguard and eyestay. Off-white pebbled leather is utilized on the signature ‘N’ logo, stitched atop a suede overlay in a pale turquoise hue. Kith branding lands on the tongue, while the label’s founder leaves his mark with a ‘Fieg’ heel inscription.

sneakers.name: New Balance 992 Kith Kithmas Teal
sneakers.story: Launching as part of the three-piece ‘Kithmas Collection,’ the Kith x New Balance 992 ‘Light Reef’ features a traditional mesh and suede upper in a vibrant turquoise finish. A contrasting tomato red accent lands on the tongue, marked with dual New Balance and Kith branding hits. The signature ‘N’ logo is rendered in dark grey pebbled leather, while ‘Fieg’ replaces traditional ‘USA’ lettering on the back heel. The sneaker’s ABZORB midsole, rendered in a clean white finish, is paired with a matching rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: New Balance 992 Kith Kithmas Red
sneakers.story: Drawn from the three-piece ‘Kithmas Collection,’ the Kith x New Balance 992 ‘Team Red’ applies a monochrome scarlet finish to an upper built with breathable mesh and soft pigskin suede. Pebbled grey leather frames the top of the tongue, marked with New Balance and Kith branding. More pebbled leather is utilized on an off-white ‘N’ logo, while the Kith founder leaves his mark with ‘Fieg’ inscribed on the back heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a two-tone ABZORB midsole.

sneakers.name: Guo Ailun x Air Jordan 35 'Morpho'
sneakers.story: The Guo Ailun x Air Jordan 35 ‘Morpho’ is a PE colorway made for the first Chinese athlete to sign with Jordan Brand. Guo’s personal logo adorns the purple padded tongue, while the sneaker’s larger design is inspired by the graceful movements of a butterfly, which nods to the guard’s effortless playing style on the hardwood. A vibrant teal finish stands out on the sneaker’s updated Eclipse Plate, offering a window to the Zoom Air units lodged in the heel and forefoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Frozen Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Frozen Blue’ applies a burst of color to Kanye West’s basketball-inspired mid-top. The layered upper features a bright blue RPU cage atop a jacquard knit upper, reinforced with synthetic suede at the toe cap. Black neoprene on the collar and tongue offers stretchy comfort, while a seamless heel counter is good for improved stability. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Boost midsole reinforced with a semi-translucent TPU cage and a herringbone traction outsole underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM BSKTBL Frozen Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Basketball ‘Frozen Blue’ highlights a pop of color on the performance-ready version of Kanye West’s futuristic hoops shoe. The upper features textile knit construction reinforced with RPU overlays, their raised wavy lines traced with vibrant blue coloring. Extra padding is added to the black neoprene collar, reinforced with a seamless heel counter that extends to a full-length Boost midsole encaged in semi-translucent TPU. Underfoot, a herringbone traction rubber outsole provides optimal grip on the hardwood.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Clay Brown’ makes use of a monofilament engineered mesh upper in a mostly black finish, accented with swooping brown stripes that extend across the side panels. They’re visible in the open spaces of the RPU cage that adds structure — and a distinctly futuristic aesthetic — to the sneaker’s bootie-like construction. The bulky EVA midsole is encapsulated in a durable PU wrap and reinforced by a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sand Taupe
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Sand Taupe’ delivers yet another in a long line of neutral colorways that have dominate the silhouette’s many releases since its global debut in 2016. Decorative no-tie laces are integrated into to the breathable Primeknit upper, featuring a patchwork-like pattern and a prominent seam that runs down the length of the vamp. On the lateral side panel, coral fibers are woven into the knit construction above the post-dyed monofilament side stripe for a subtle pop of color. A fully caged Boost midsole provides lightweight cushioning.

sneakers.name: Jordan XXXV Titan
sneakers.story: Celebrating the Manila-based retailer’s decade in business, the Titan x Air Jordan 35 PF ‘10th Anniversary’ showcases a premium build that combines translucent textile with genuine leather and suede. Titan’s lightning bolt logo is debossed on the lateral heel, while a protruding heel tab in Bright Crimson is stamped with three gold stars in a nod to the Philippines. Additional crimson accents land on the pull loop atop the tongue and the Flightwire cables that radiate outward from the Eclipse Plate 2.0, its polished surface treated to a subtle off-white finish.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte’ features an eye-catching color scheme that strays from the signature Yeezy palette, which traditionally leans heavily on muted earth tones. A splash of fluorescent green is applied to the the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, contrasted by the camo-like tan and yellow composition that makes up the Primeknit upper. Standard Boost cushioning is enveloped in grey rubber and reinforced with a herringbone-traction outsole. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Non-Reflective’ utilizes a re-engineered Primeknit upper finished in muddy brown tones. A contrasting splash of royal blue distinguishes the translucent monofilament window that’s woven into the lateral side of the sock-like construction. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, featuring an elevated heel for a fluid transition. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole provides grippy traction. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Non-Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Europe.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Non-Reflective’ features a contrasting blend of brown and slate hues on a breathable Primeknit upper designed to wrap around the foot in lightweight support. A yellow finish is applied to the translucent monofilament window that cuts through the lateral side, complete with a series of large perforations for enhanced air flow. Underfoot, cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole reveals the sneaker’s full-length Boost cushioning. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Non-Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Asia Pacific, Africa, the Middle East, and India.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Reflective’ showcases a pop of color on an otherwise subdued design, highlighted by a splash of royal blue on the signature translucent monofilament window. The rest of the upper is rendered in brown Primeknit, which weaves in reflective fibers for added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber and reinforced with a herringbone traction outsole underfoot. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Europe.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘LMNTE Reflective’ adds a hi-vis element to Kanye West’s lifestyle sneaker, featuring slip-on construction designed to hug the foot in lightweight support. Reflective threads are woven into the mostly brown Primeknit upper, accented with mustard yellow coloring throughout the translucent monofilament window. The minimalist build is mounted atop a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent cage for added durability. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Asia Pacific, Africa, the Middle East, and India.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte Glow
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an energetic color scheme made up of yellow and tan hues throughout the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The resulting camo-like design is treated to a green-tinged glow-in-the-dark finish, matching the dayglow shade applied to the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window. The bright tones are tempered by the midsole, featuring full-length Boost encased in dark grey rubber. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro Low Golf Black Metallic
Zion Williamson x Air Jordan 35 'Bayou Boys'
sneakers.story: The Zion Williamson x Air Jordan 35 ‘Bayou Boys’ is a sequel colorway to the athlete’s Air Jordan 34 PE, both of which celebrate Zion joining the New Orleans Pelicans. The standout detail on the upper is a cracked faux gator leather overlay, arcing from heel to toe and encircling the sneaker’s Flightwire system. A marbled green finish is utilized on the Eclipse Plate 2.0, which gives way to a gum rubber outsole featuring a best-in-class herringbone traction pattern.

sneakers.name: Zion Williamson x Air Jordan 35 PF 'Bayou Boys'
sneakers.story: The Zion Williamson x Air Jordan 35 PF ‘Bayou Boys’ brings back the New Orleans-inspired design theme introduced through one of the NBA athlete’s Air Jordan 34 PE colorways that released to the public. This pair celebrates the Mississippi delta with an upper that blends black textile with Lime Blast accents and crackled premium leather overlays, the latter joined by an iridescent connector piece. A marbled green finish distinguishes the Eclipse Plate 2.0, which extends to the gum rubber outsole underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ delivers a subdued rendition of the minimalist lifestyle sneaker. A charcoal grey finish dominates the re-engineered Primeknit upper, with inky black and a subtle streak of navy blue surrounding the translucent monofilament window. The sock-like build sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, encaged in semi-translucent rubber and supported underfoot by a herringbone traction outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Onyx Reflective’ makes use of a re-engineered Primeknit upper in a blend of black and mahogany tones. Semi-translucent woven construction distinguishes the post dyed monofilament side stripe that accents the lateral side panel, while reflective fibers add a high-vis element to the murky palette. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a smoky rubber cage and reinforced by a herringbone gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Nizza Hi Human Made Off White
sneakers.story: Conceived in partnership with the workwear-inspired brand founded by Nigo, the Human Made x adidas Nizza High ‘Off White’ delivers a monochrome colorway of the retro silhouette. Ivory-hued canvas is utilized on the upper, secured with a combination of traditional laces and a medial-side zipper, which opens up to reveal ‘adidas by Nigo’ in Japanese text. A repeating pattern of Human Made’s heart logo adorns the gum rubber overlay that wraps around the midsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Safflower’ showcases a mostly neutral color scheme in keeping with the Yeezy brand’s signature palette. Subtle hints of color arrive via yellow striations throughout the monofilament engineered mesh upper, overlaid with a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage that extends from heel to toe. The sneaker’s interior bootie construction is rendered in a contrasting black finish, offering a snug, comfortable fit. A PU encapsulated EVA midsole anchors the streamlined silhouette.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Fade
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Fade’ makes use of a patterned Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of beige and brown tones. The sneaker’s post-dyed monofilament side stripe is treated to an indigo finish, offering added breathability and a subtle pop of color. Standard adidas Boost cushioning is utilized on the midsole, entirely wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage for improved support and stability. This colorway is exlusive to the Asia-Pacific region

sneakers.name: adidas Superstar Craig Green Off White
sneakers.story: Launching as part of a larger collection with the British fashion designer, the Craig Green x adidas Superstar ‘Off White Bright Red’ treats the shell-toed sneaker icon to a comprehensive makeover, highlighted by contrast stitching throughout the off-white microsuede upper. Conventional eyelets are paired with grey webbing lace loops, while the sneaker’s signature three-stripes are formed with bright orange embroidery. Stitched detailing continues on the rubber cuspule.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 35 PF 'Bred'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 35 PF ‘Bred’ updates the performance hoops shoe in a familiar two-tone color combination rooted in Jordan Brand heritage. The upper is crafted from black textile with tonal suede overlays and Flightwire cables stitched into the side panels. Jumpman branding appears on iridescent detailing on the lateral collar and a reflective silver tongue inspired by the Air Jordan 5. Responsive cushioning is provided by Zoom Air units under the heel and forefoot, visible via an Eclipse plate in a gradient blend of black and red. This PF version is exclusive to Asia and features an extra-durable red rubber outsole made for outdoor courts.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 10 Retro MCS Low 'Black White'
adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Calcite Glow
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Calcite Glow’ highlights a neutral combination of white and grey tones on the breathable Primeknit upper, complete with camo-like glow-in-the-dark detailing that’s revealed when the lights go out. A dark grey finish distinguishes the translucent monofilament window on the sneaker’s side panel, matching the sock-like collar that provides a snug fit around the ankle. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning with each step.

sneakers.name: Shoe Surgeon x Air Jordan 1 High 'Freddy Krueger' Custom
Vans Old Skool Notre Off-White
sneakers.story: A joint venture with the Chicago-based retailer, the Notre x Vans Vault OG Old Skool LX ‘Off White’ features a monochrome neutral finish on a hairy suede upper, complete with tonal canvas on the medial side panel. Vans’ signature side stripe is reworked in Notre’s signature handshake motif, symbolizing themes of unity and teamwork. The low-top rests on an off-white vulcanized rubber midsole, accented with a vintage license plate at the heel.

sneakers.name: adidas Nite Jogger Beyonce Ivy Park Off White
sneakers.story: Launching as part of a capsule collection with Beyoncé’s activewear brand, the Ivy Park x adidas Nite Jogger ‘Ecru Tint’ delivers an understate colorway of the retro-inspired runner. The lightweight upper, constructed from off-white textile with suede overlays in contrasting black and green hues, features a unique toggle lacing system that incorporates a braided pull tab that wraps around the heel. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning with each step.

sneakers.name: Jordan 5 Retro OFF-WHITE Sail
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Virgil Abloh’s luxury streetwear label, the Off-White x Air Jordan 5 Retro SP 'Sail' represents the follow-up to the partner brands’ black AJ5 from early 2020. This pair makes use of a layered textile upper in a subtle cream finish, complete with circular cutouts on the midfoot, collar and silver reflective tongue. Virgil’s signature flourishes, including printed Helvetica text on the medial side panel, complement ‘23’ and Nike Air branding on the heel. A pre-yellowed translucent outsole adds to the sneaker’s vintage aesthetic.

sneakers.name: Jordan XXXV Fragment
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Hiroshi Fujiwara’s influential label, the Fragment Design x Air Jordan 35 ‘Base Grey’ utilizes a familiar palette originally featured on the creative partners’ highly coveted Air Jordan 1 from 2014. The shoe’s design is centered around the redesigned Flight Plate, encircled in Kurim detailing and reinforced with leather overlays in black and royal blue. Traditional Jumpman branding adorns the tongue, while a woven tag bearing Fragment’s lightning bolt logo extends out from the back heel.

sneakers.name: Off-White Out of Office Low 'White Purple'
Off-White Out of Office Low 'White Cream'
Off-White Out of Office Low 'For Walking - White Black'
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT League of Legends (Esports)
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Natural
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Natural’ presents an understated colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, featuring a stretchy Primeknit upper in a blend of varying cream and beige tones. On the sneaker’s lateral side, a post-dyed monofilament side stripe adds a see-through element to the lightweight build. Details include no-tie bungee laces and adidas’ three-stripe branding on the interior heel. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a yellow-tinted rubber cage, delivers a responsive ride.

sneakers.name: Jordan XXXV Dynasties
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 35 ‘Dynasties’ celebrate the 600th anniversary of the Forbidden City, an imperial palace of the Ming and Qing dynasties, located in the center of Beijing. The sneaker’s design takes inspiration from the architecture of the palace complex, featuring suede overlays inspired by yellow tiled roofs and red accents that give the nod to crimson pillars, doors and windows. The sneaker’s signature Eclipse plate is rendered in a glossy black finish, separating the yellow midsole and translucent jade outsole.

sneakers.name: Jordan XXXV Warrior
sneakers.story: The Rui Hachimura x Air Jordan 35 ‘Warrior’ is a PE colorway made for the Japanese-born NBA athlete. The two-tone red and black design references Rui’s half-Japanese, half-Beninese background, while his Kanji-inspired personal logo adorns the tongue and sockliner. The shoe’s split coloring is repeated in gradient fashion on the signature Eclipse Plate, providing an open window to the springy Zoom Air units in the heel and forefoot.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 35 'Center Of Gravity'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 35 ‘Center of Gravity’ represents the silhouette’s debut colorway, one that nods to the Air Jordan 5 on the occasion of its 30th anniversary. The sneaker is appointed with a number of heritage details, including a grey suede overlay, ‘23’ heel branding and a tongue and collar modeled after the AJ5. In terms of performance, a Flightwire system is layered atop a Kurim cage for a locked-in fit. The midsole is updated with an enlarged Eclipse Plate 2.0, complete with visible Zoom Air cushioning in the heel and forefoot.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 35 SP TP PF 'Center of Gravity'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 35 SP TP PF ‘Center of Gravity’ features vibrant hues on a lightweight build centered around the stabilizing Eclipse Plate 2.0, which extends up the midsole for lateral structure and support. Additional performance benefits include Flightwire cables for improved lockdown and Zoom Air cushioning under the heel and forefoot. Exclusive to the Asian market, this PF version makes use of an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor courts.

sneakers.name: ZX 2K Flux 'Grey Off White'
sneakers.story: The adidas ZX 2K Flux ‘Grey Off White’ treats the retro-inspired silhouette to an entirely neutral palette, highlighted by a breathable knit upper rendered in varying shades of grey. TPU overlays along the toe and heel offer structural support, while reflective three-stripes provide added visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a dual-density adiPRENE X midsole in a tonal grey finish.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Teal Blue
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Teal Blue’ delivers a lifestyle variation of Kanye West’s performance hoops shoe, highlighted by a patterned knit upper that blends bright teal accents with varying shades of grey. A tonal suede overlay adds durability along the toe, while a pronounced heel counter in a contrasting black finish provides rearfoot support. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole encased in semi-translucent rubber.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Carbon’ features a breathable Primeknit upper in a neutral black and grey finish. The sneaker’s lateral side features a streak of black via the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, separating a light grey weave up top with mostly black construction on the lower half. No-tie bungee laces deliver a secure fit. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a yellow-tinged rubber cage.

sneakers.name: Russell Westbrook x Air Jordan 16 Retro 'Why Not?'
sneakers.story: Taken from a two-piece pack that also includes a Converse Chuck 70, the Russell Westbrook x Air Jordan 16 Retro ‘Why Not?’ makes use of an all-black design inspired by the athlete’s leather jackets. A magnetic shroud wraps over the midfoot, covered in tonal embroidery that mimics the look of chain nets found on outdoor basketball courts — detailing that speaks to Westbrook’s gritty style of play. Metallic silver studs on the lateral side reflects his flashy personal style.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Rubber Dunk Off-White UNC
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Virgil Abloh’s luxury streetwear brand, the Off-White x Nike Air Rubber Dunk ‘University Blue’ reimagines the retro low-top with design elements borrowed from the lifestyle running space. The latter includes an upper taken from the P-6000, rendered in white mesh with blue accents and metallic silver overlays, and visible Air cushioning in the gum rubber cupsole. Virgil leaves his personal stamp via an orange tab on the outlined Swoosh and Helvetica text on the medial side panel.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Rubber Dunk Off-White University Gold
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Virgil Abloh’s luxury streetwear brand, the Off-White x Nike Air Rubber Dunk ‘University Gold’ showcases a comprehensive reworking of the retro silhouette, highlighted by an upper inspired by the P-6000 runner. A yellow mesh base is fortified with metallic gold leather overlays and an outlined Swoosh. Contrasting black branding, including a ‘Nike Off’ tongue tag and Virgil’s signature Helvetica text on the medial side, is matched by a solid black midsole with visible Air cushioning.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Rubber Dunk Off-White Green Strike
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Virgil Abloh’s luxury streetwear brand, the Off-White x Nike Air Rubber Dunk ‘Green Strike’ delivers a reconstructed take on the classic silhouette, one that incorporates the layered upper of the P-6000 runner. The sneaker’s mostly black palette is disrupted by vibrant green accents, including an outlined Swoosh, ‘Nike Off’ branding on the tongue tag and self-referential ‘Shoelaces’ text. The eye-catching hue is repeated on the sneaker’s tooling, where it frames a visible Air sole unit.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Lucky Green'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Lucky Green’ makes use of a familiar design that calls to mind Ray Allen’s coveted Air ‘Three-Point Record’ PE from 2011. The upper combines white tumbled leather with green synthetic suede, supported underfoot by the silhouette’s signature panther paw outsole in black rubber. Branding hits include a green embroidered Jumpman atop the tongue, matching the circular hologram on the lateral ankle.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air Cadence Pale Ivory
sneakers.story: The Jordan Air Cadence ‘Pale Ivory’ showcases vivid accents on a lifestyle runner built for everyday wear. A flash of hot pink marks the visible Air sole unit nestled in the heel of the soft foam midsole, reinforced underfoot with a two-tone rubber outsole. Up top, off-white mesh is fortified with black nubuck overlays covered in a tonal crackle print. A padded collar combines with a soft tongue and molded footbed to deliver a comfortable fit.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper Non-Reflective’ applies a neutral color scheme to its breathable Primeknit upper, featuring a snug, sock-like fit that allows for a secure fit with or without laces. A muddy tan finish distinguishes the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, allowing the signature detail to stand out against a knit backdrop in lighter grey and Off-White tones. A full-length Boost midsole supports the lightweight build, equipped with a raised heel for a smooth ride.

sneakers.name: Chron Solarsoft SB Premium 'Off Noir Grey'
sneakers.story: The Nike Chron Solarsoft SB Premium ‘Off Noir Grey’ treats the no-frills skate shoe to an unassuming color scheme, highlighted by varying shades of grey on an upper constructed from textile and suede. The neutral hues throughout the shoe’s exterior are contrasted by a multicolor striped design on the collar lining. Underfoot, a Solarsoft insole provides lightweight cushioning, while the rubber outsole makes use of a circular herringbone pattern for superior traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper Reflective’ offers sock-like comfort on the upper, crafted from subtly patterned Primeknit in a blend of light grey and beige hues. Reflective fibers are woven into the mix, offering enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A coppery finish distinguishes the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, adding a see-through element to the minimalist build. A greyish-blue rubber cage envelops the full-length Boost midsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Arzareth’ features vibrant blue tones on a breathable knit upper, its side panels overlaid with a semi-translucent RPU cage for added structure and durability. Contrasting black is applied to the sneaker’s bootie-style collar, good for a snug fit around the ankle. The sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole for grippy traction.

sneakers.name: Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Off Noir'
sneakers.colorway: Off Noir/Brigade Blue/Dark Smoke Grey/Light Fusion Red
sneakers.story: The Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Off Noir’ represents the follow-up effort to the duo’s highly coveted Air Jordan 1 collaboration from 2018. The updated design features a black suede upper with matching black mesh on the toe box and blue mesh around the collar. The semi-translucent structural wings are attached to molded red eyelets, matching the woven Air Jordan tag atop the padded tongue and Nike Air branding on the heel. The TPU wings are filled in, reminiscent of an original Tinker Hatfield sketch of the AJ4, while the AIR JORDAN tag usually found on the inside of the tongue conveys a unique look, like someone folded the tongue over to expose the inside tag. Finally, a 'UN/LA' tag on the side panel shows the Union heritage and a yellowed midsole conveys a vintage aesthetic.

sneakers.name: Jordan 4 Retro Union Off Noir
sneakers.colorway: Off-Noir/Brigade Blue-Dark Smoke Grey-Light Fusion Red
sneakers.story: The Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Off Noir’ represents the follow-up effort to the duo’s highly coveted Air Jordan 1 collaboration from 2018. The updated design features a black suede upper with matching black mesh on the toe box and blue mesh around the collar. The semi-translucent structural wings are attached to molded red eyelets, matching the woven Air Jordan tag atop the padded tongue and Nike Air branding on the heel. The TPU wings are filled in, reminiscent of an original Tinker Hatfield sketch of the AJ4, while the AIR JORDAN tag usually found on the inside of the tongue conveys a unique look, like someone folded the tongue over to expose the inside tag. Finally, a 'UN/LA' tag on the side panel shows the Union heritage and a yellowed midsole conveys a vintage aesthetic.

sneakers.name: Jordan Delta Mid Union Off Noir
sneakers.colorway: Off Noir/Brigade Blue-Dark Smoke Grey-Light Fusion Red
sneakers.story: Made in partnership with the venerable menswear boutique, the Union LA x Jordan Delta Mid ‘Off Noir’ features the same colors and materials utilized on the duo’s Air Jordan 4 collaboration. The lifestyle silhouette carries a predominantly black upper crafted from mesh and suede. Contrasting pops of royal blue and crimson make their way to the collar and heel overlay, respectively, while Union branding stands out in yellow on the lateral heel and tongue. Responsive cushioning arrives via a React foam midsole.

sneakers.name: Nike SB Bruin React Black White
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Israfil’ features a patchwork-like composition on the Primeknit upper, constructed from a two-tone blend of tan and grey yarns. The neutral hues are enlivened by a streak of yellow on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of the standard full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent rubber sidewall. A grippy gum rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot.

sneakers.name: Jordan 5 Retro Alternate Bel-Air
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Alternate Bel-Air’ follows in the footsteps of the original ‘Bel-Air’ Air Jordan 5 from 2013, featuring a ‘90s-inspired color scheme paying homage to Will Smiths’ NBC sitcom, ‘The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air.’ The classic mid-top sports a white leather upper mounted atop a contrasting purple midsole with visible Air cushioning. Mismatched vibrant accents are applied to the interior lining, Jumpman branding hits and embroidered ‘23’ on the lateral heel.

sneakers.name: Air Max Janoski 2 SB 'Off Noir Cerulean'
Jordan Air Cadence White Vast Grey
adidas Type 0-5 0AMC Off White
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Luke Meier’s menswear brand, the OAMC x adidas Type 05 ‘Off White’ weds sleek minimalism with rugged functionality. Various tan and off-white shades are applied to the upper, constructed from mesh, polyester and nubuck. Semi-translucent TPU pieces add lightweight support along the midfoot and heel. The sneaker rides on a sculpted foam midsole, reinforced with an EVA adiPRENE heel and a lugged Traxion outsole underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Type 0-4 0AMC Off White
sneakers.story: Designed in partnership with OAMC, the adidas Type 04 ‘Off White’ features an understated color scheme on an outdoor trail shoe built with sandal-like comfort. Translucent mesh inserts and cut-out detailing are built into the leather upper for added breathability, while a burgundy pull loop and contrast yellow stitching offer subtle pops of color. The hybrid silhouette rides on an adiPRENE midsole, supported underfoot by a gum rubber Traxion outsole.

sneakers.name: Nike Benassi Stussy Off Noir
sneakers.story: Drawn from a larger capsule collection with the long-running streetwear brand, the Stussy x Nike Benassi ‘Off Noir’ delivers an essential colorway of the classic slip-on. The iconic Stussy wordmark is stamped in white on the synthetic leather strap, lined in soft jersey for a comfortable fit. Tonal Nike branding adorns the contoured footbed, supported by a Phylon foam midsole for lightweight cushioning.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air Zoom Renegade White Infrared 23 Black
sneakers.story: Designed for athletes who run as part of their training regimen, the Jordan Air Zoom Renegade ‘Flash Crimson’ features nano-printed designs on a color-blocked upper built with a lightweight blend of textile and synthetic materials. A full-length plate enhances the cushioning properties of the foam midsole, equipped with dual Zoom Air units under the ball of the foot. Flex grooves built into the rubber outsole accommodate the natural motion of the foot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Blue Oat Non-Reflective’ utilizes a sock-like Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of beige and orange tones. The sneaker’s signature translucent monofilament window stands out in a contrasting blue finish, complete with perforated detailing for improved breathability. The one-piece build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a semi-translucent cage and reinforced by a gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG co.JP 'Tokyo' Japan Release
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG co.JP 'Tokyo' Japan Release makes use of a familiar color scheme that recalls a Japan-exclusive colorway from 2001. Unlike the original, the design replaces a Jumpman atop the tongue with Nike Air branding. The rest of the upper combines matte grey leather with a metallic silver finish on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar flap. The latter is adorned with a jeweled Jordan Wings logo on the sneaker’s lateral side.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Blue Oat Reflective’ makes use of a Primeknit upper in a blend of orange and brown hues, resulting in a unique camo-like pattern that’s enlivened with a contrasting pop of blue on the translucent monofilament window. Reflective thread is woven into the sock-like build, offering added visibility in low-light conditions. The responsive Boost midsole is encased in semi-translucent rubber and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Zyon’ showcases various woven patterns on the breathable Primeknit upper, executed in a subdued blend of earth tones. The collar is trimmed in neutral grey, while the signature post-dyed monofilament stripe cuts through the sneaker’s lateral side in a dark brown finish. Full-length Boost cushioning is visible through the semi-translucent rubber midsole, reinforced underfoot by a gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Nike React Presto Black White Off Noir
adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Bone’ makes use of a high-contrast color scheme, highlighted by a cream polyester upper with black no-sew overlays at the toe and heel. No-tie bungee laces provide easy on and off, while reflective 700 branding on the sneaker’s quarter panel offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The seamless build rests on a sculpted black PU midsole, which houses drop-in Boost cushioning for a smooth ride.

sneakers.name: adidas Niteball Off White Cream White
sneakers.story: The adidas Niteball ‘Cream White Pink Tint’ showcases reflective accents on a lifestyle sneaker inspired by durable basketball shoes built for the blacktop. Exaggerated three-stripe detailing stands out on the leather and suede upper, mounted atop a sculpted Lightstrike midsole for plush cushioning. Interior bootie construction works in tandem with an integrated lacing system to deliver a secure, comfortable fit.

sneakers.name: Nike Kyrie 6 USA White
sneakers.story: The Nike Kyrie 6 ‘USA’ treats Kyrie Irving’s sixth signature shoe to a patriotic makeover, highlighted by a white mesh and leather upper with contrasting blue and red accents. The latter hue is applied to the sneaker’s molded heel piece and adjustable midfoot strap, good for added support and a lockdown fit. The mid-top rides on a soft foam midsole that packs a Nike Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot for responsive cushioning.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Ararat
sneakers.story: Debuting at London Fashion Week in February 2020, the Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Ararat’ launched without warning the following June through Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply website. The molded slip-on is constructed from a unique foam compound that blends lightweight EVA with harvested algae. Sculpted lines and a neutral monochromatic finish promote a streamlined, futuristic aesthetic, while a series of oval cut-outs enable airflow for ventilated comfort.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium
sneakers.story: A performance basketball shoe envisaged by Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Barium’ features a dull green Primeknit upper overlaid with semi-translucent detailing for a fluid, dynamic look. Black no-sew overlays at the toe and heel provide seamless, lightweight support, while interior bootie construction deliver a snug fit. The sneaker rides atop a caged Boost midsole, reinforced underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro SE 'Animal Instinct 2.0'
sneakers.story: A sequel to the wildlife-inspired December 2019 colorway, the Air Jordan 3 Retro SE ‘Animal Instinct 2.0’ features a number of different exotic prints on the upper. They include a croc-textured black leather base, tonal ostrich-skin mudguard and grey snakeskin on the forefoot overlay. Mocha brown coloring on Jordan Brand’s iconic elephant print is contrasted by a bright yellow heel panel and scaly green collar.

sneakers.name: Jordan Zoom Trunner Advance Bel-Air
sneakers.story: The Jordan Zoom Trunner Advance ‘Bel-Air’ showcases a vibrant ‘90s-inspired color scheme on a lightweight training shoe built for speed and stability. The breathable white mesh upper, reinforced with tonal no-sew overlays at the toe and heel, sits on a foam midsole with a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot. The lateral sidewall is bolstered with an external diamond-pattern cage that offers added support during side-to-side movements.

sneakers.name: Nike Owaysis Black White
sneakers.story: The Nike Owaysis Sandal ‘Black’ uses open construction for breathable comfort during the summertime months. The two-piece upper is built with black synthetic leather, complete with an adjustable heel strap for a custom fit. Nike branding adorns the vamp and webbing pull tab that delivers easy on and off. A contrasting white finish is applied to the dual-density foam midsole, built with flex grooves for a smooth ride.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Max 90 One of One
sneakers.story: The Nike Air Max 90 ‘DIY Flare’ makes use of a special rub-off top layer on the sneaker’s pink leather mudguard. After extended wear – or the application of acetone, for those who want immediate results – the pastel finish gives way to a Bright Crimson base. The rest of the upper is crafted from breathable white mesh with tonal leather overlays and TPU accents in Hydrogen Blue. This pair dropped alongside a matching Air Max 97 with the same wear-away pink mudguard.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Max 97 One of One
sneakers.story: The Nike Air Max 97 ‘DIY Flare’ offers an opportunity for personal customization, thanks to the use of a rub-off outer layer on the sneaker’s pink leather mudguard. The soft pastel hues up top are complemented by an icy translucent rubber outsole, providing durable traction underneath the signature full-length Max Air unit. The kicks dropped alongside a matching Air Max 90, complete with the same wear-away pink mudguard.

sneakers.name: Jordan Maxin 200 Camo
sneakers.story: The Jordan Maxin 200 ‘Camo’ features a retro-inspired design that blends details that call to mind legacy Jordan silhouettes. The upper combines glossy black patent leather with camo-print suede overlays and molded quarter-panel grills reminiscent of the Air Jordan 5. An Off-White foam midsole, housing a visible Max Air unit in the heel, rides on a herringbone traction outsole with translucent rubber in high-wear areas.

sneakers.name: Jordan Dub Zero Camo
sneakers.story: The Jordan Dub Zero ‘Olive Camo’ delivers a military-inspired take on the hybrid silhouette originally released in 2005. The sneaker’s olive green patent leather upper is overlaid with suede paneling finished in a traditional woodland camo print, replacing the signature laser-etched designs inspired by the Air Jordan 20. It all rides on a familiar two-tone midsole borrowed from the Air Jordan 4, complete with a visible Air sole unit in the heel.

sneakers.name: Nike SuperRep Cycle White Black
sneakers.story: Made for indoor cycling, the Nike SuperRep Cycle ‘White Black’ utilizes breathable construction designed to prevent overheating. Cooling features include lightweight mesh up top and a series of vents in the outsole. Adjustable straps provide a secure fit during intense pedaling, while a stiff internal plate delivers enhanced energy return underneath the foot. The external plate is compatible with two standard types of cleats.

sneakers.name: New Balance 998 Kith Spring 2
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with Ronnie Fieg’s retail establishment and brand, the Kith x New Balance 998 Made in USA ‘Steel Blue’ borrows the familiar color scheme of the iconic 1300CL. The retro runner sports a traditional build that combines a pale blue mesh base with pigskin suede paneling in charcoal grey. A double-layer ‘N’ logo graces the quarter panel, featuring a white reflective top layer outlined in slate blue. A lightweight ABZORB midsole anchors the two-tone design.

sneakers.name: New Balance 992 Kith Spring 2
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with the NYC-based retailer, the Kith x New Balance 992 Made in USA ‘Steel Blue’ makes use of a familiar color palette inspired by the iconic 1300CL. The traditional build, combining a pale blue mesh base with charcoal grey suede overlays throughout, features a reflective white ‘N’ logo outlined in slate blue. The mixed-material upper rides on a two-tone ABZORB SBS midsole for lightweight cushioning.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Tyrian
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Tyrian’ makes use of a mixed-material build, featuring a purplish-blue elastane base with contrasting overlays in black leather and brown suede. A padded collar and tongue combine for a comfortable fit, while a rubber wrap at the base of the upper provides added durability and abrasion resistance. The podular midsole utilizes adiPRENE+ technology for impact absorption and high-rebound cushioning.

sneakers.name: ACG Air Deschutz 'Black Off Noir'
sneakers.story: The Nike ACG Deschutz ‘Black Off Noir’ brings back a 1992 slip-on that combines the breezy wearability of a sandal with the performance capabilities of a sneaker. To that end, the foam midsole houses an encapsulated Air sole unit in the heel, while an outdoor-ready rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot. The multi-strap system up top is constructed from hydrophobic materials that keep feet dry and comfortable.

sneakers.name: SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro '10th Anniversary'
sneakers.story: Celebrating the Miami-based retailer’s first decade in business, the SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro ‘10th Anniversary’ features a design inspired by Miami’s Freedom Tower. The all-suede upper, finished in Sail and beige coloring, recalls the structure’s two-tone façade, while a newsprint graphic on the outsole references the building’s origins as the headquarters of The Miami News. Unique branding hits include ‘SOLEFLY 10’ stamped on the tongue and the shop’s logo embroidered on the left heel.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sulfur
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Sulfur’ utilizes a breathable Primeknit upper in a yellowish tan hue, accented with the sneaker’s signature monofilament side stripe in olive green. A pull tab at the heel complements the sock-like collar to deliver easy on and off. Underneath the foot, a full-length Boost unit provides responsive cushioning. The foam compound is visible through cut-out detailing on the gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 Low 'Heritage'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 Low ‘Heritage’ applies a familiar color scheme to the performance hoops shoe. The upper is constructed from a blend of semi-translucent black textile with matching black suede overlays at the toe and heel. An exposed padded collar distinguishes the low-top from its full-height counterpart, while the pull loop and layered tongue remain intact. The latter is embellished with silver Jumpman branding and a classic Flight logo in red.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 Low 'Heritage'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 Low ‘Heritage’ gets dressed in a simple two-tone color scheme, executed on a build that’s mostly unchanged from the sneaker’s full-height counterpart. The upper, constructed from semi-translucent black textile, features a lower collar and an added suede toe cap. Laser Orange accents are applied to the tongue and heel panel, treated to a subtle iridescent finish and marked with a raised Jumpman logo in black.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 Low PF 'Heritage'
sneakers.story: Riding atop a wear-resistant rubber outsole, the Air Jordan 34 Low PF ‘Heritage’ is specially made for play on outdoor courts. The upper, constructed from translucent black textile with tonal synthetic suede overlays, features reflective detailing for added visibility in low-light conditions. The tooling is unchanged from the inline 34, featuring a Zoom Air unit below the forefoot that’s visible through the Eclipse plate.

sneakers.name: adidas SC Premiere Extra Butter Cableknit Off White
sneakers.story: Made in collaboration with the New York-based retailer, the Extra Butter x adidas SC Premiere ‘Core White’ features a cable-knit Primeknit upper developed exclusively for the joint venture. The revised design loses the signature lateral-side logo window while adding white leather overlays and a woven adidas tag. EB branding is stamped in gold-foil lettering on the tongue tag and navy leather heel tab, the latter accompanied by a jacquard woven heel stripe.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Phosphor’ showcases an eye-catching neon yellow finish on the polyester upper, accented with oversized reflective silver ‘700’ branding. Contrasting black no-sew overlays provide lightweight durability at the toe and heel, while no-tie bungee laces offer a secure fit. A webbing pull tab is good for easy on and off. The seamless upper rides on a sculpted black PU midsole, enhanced with full-length drop-in Boost cushioning.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Linen
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Linen’ showcases a pale yellow hue on the sneaker’s breathable Primeknit upper, accented with reflective detailing on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. The lining, as well as the reinforced trim around the collar, are both finished in slate blue coloring. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, encapsulated in semi-translucent rubber cage and supported underfoot by a gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Earth Brown
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Slides ‘Earth Brown’ showcase a subdued monochromatic finish on the slip-on design. Built for everyday wear, the versatile sandal is constructed from EVA foam with a molded footbed for immediate step-in comfort. Underfoot, the outsole uses exaggerated flex grooves for enhanced traction. This pair dropped alongside accompanying colorways in ‘Bone,’ ‘Resin’ and ‘Desert Sand,’ with the latter available exclusively at Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply site.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 Low 'Pure Money'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 Low ‘Pure Money’ showcases a pristine color scheme that recalls the white-on-white Air Jordan 4 originally released in 2006. Here, the monochromatic finish is disrupted by a number of subtle accents, including black eyelets, metallic silver Jumpman branding and neon green detailing that seeps through the semi-translucent textile upper. Additional pops of bright green appear on the midsole and sockliner.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 Low PF 'Pure Money'
sneakers.story: Featuring an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor courts, the Air Jordan 34 Low PF ‘Pure Money’ features a pristine color scheme inspired by the classic white-on-white Air Jordan 4 from 2006. This low-top edition is mostly unchanged from the inline 34, save for an exposed padded collar, synthetic leather toe cap and revised heel panel. Vibrant pops of Electric Green are mostly kept under wraps, appearing on the sockliner and rubber outsole

sneakers.name: Nike Blazer Low Leather White Black
adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah
sneakers.story: The Yeezy 700 V3 'Alvah' delivers a stealthy colorway of Kanye West’s sculpted silhouette. A black and grey mesh upper is fortified with glow-in-the-dark RPU overlays for structural support. Interior bootie construction is good for a snug, comfortable fit, while reflective accents at the base of the tongue deliver added visibility in low-light conditions. Forgoing Boost cushioning, the sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Hare'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Hare' delivers an understated take on the classic silhouette with a championship pedigree. Monochromatic grey coloring is applied to the suede upper, appointed with traditional AJ6 details that include lace locks, perforated inlays and an extended spoiler at the heel. A two-tone midsole, finished in contrasting white and True Red tones, is supported by a translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder Reflective
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Cinder Reflective’ delivers a stealthy colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, highlighted by a Primeknit upper in a charcoal grey finish. The bootie-style construction of the collar is complemented by a pull tab for easy on and off, while the signature post-dyed side stripe is treated to a light-grabbing reflective finish for added visibility. A full-length Boost midsole, encased in a dark grey rubber cage, is visible through cut-outs in the gum rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 'Mist Non-Reflective' utilizes a breathable Primeknit upper finished in a camo-like pattern comprising neutral grey and tan hues. Details include a sock-like collar, rope laces integrated directly into the knit build and perforated detailing on the side panels for ventilated comfort. A semi-translucent rubber cage is applied to the full-length Boost midsole, featuring an elevated heel for a forward-leaning stance. A gum rubber outsole is good for grippy traction underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Cinder Non-Reflective’ delivers a muted colorway of Kanye West’s popular lifestyle silhouette. A charcoal grey hue is applied throughout the Primeknit upper, accented with the standard post-dyed monofilament stripe on the sneaker’s lateral side. The same dark grey coloring is used on the rubber cage that encapsulates the Boost midsole, while the outsole is rendered in grippy gum rubber. Underfoot, an unexpected pop of bright yellow distinguishes the heel pod.

sneakers.name: Nike Kyrie 6 White Black
sneakers.story: The Kyrie 6 'Oreo' showcases a simple black and white color scheme on Kyrie Irving’s sixth signature shoe. The white leather and mesh upper is accented by a black embroidered Nike Swoosh and black speckling on the adjustable midfoot strap, good for enhanced containment and a locked-in feel. The black rubber outsole curves up and over the sidewall of the foam midsole, which houses an Air Zoom Turbo unit at the forefoot for springy cushioning.

sneakers.name: Nike Zoom Freak 1 White Black
sneakers.story: The Zoom Freak 1 'Oreo' highlights a simple black and white color scheme throughout Giannis Antetokounmpo's debut signature shoe. The breathable white mesh upper is supported by contrasting black and white internal bands for a lockdown fit, while the speckled foam midsole packs double-stacked Zoom Air units at the heel for extra-responsive cushioning. The black and white theme continues underfoot on the durable rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Desert Sage' is outfitted in a pale green Primeknit upper with tonal rope laces and reflective detailing on the sneaker’s signature side stripe. Contrast pops of color emerge on the orange collar lining and sockliner, the latter printed with dual adidas and Yeezy branding. The minimalist build sits atop full-length Boost midsole, encased in tonal green rubber with grippy gum rubber on the outsole.

sneakers.name: Nike LD Waffle Sacai White Nylon
sneakers.story: Launching in March 2020, the Sacai x LDWaffle 'White Nylon' is the neutral follow-up to one of Nike’s most sought-after sneaker collaborations from 2019. The hybrid silhouette, combining the Nike LDV and Waffle Racer, features a white nylon upper with leather and suede overlays at the toe and heel. The Swoosh, laces and tongue are similarly double layered, while an elongated midsole adds to the sneaker’s eye-catching look.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 'Infrared 23'
