sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 ‘Infrared 23’ serves up a distinctive colorway with a championship pedigree. The design represents a flip on the ‘Infrared’ Air Jordan 6, the shoe that Michael wore in 1991 when he clinched his first ever NBA title. Here, the vibrant red hue acts as the sneaker’s base color, while contrasting black accents appear on the tongue, heel panel and midsole. ‘Flight’ and Nike Air branding strengthen the connection to Jordan Brand heritage.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Infrared 23'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 PF ‘Infrared 23’ boasts a championship pedigree, featuring the same combination of colors used on the Air Jordan 6 that Michael wore when he clinched his first NBA title back in 1991. Here, Infrared is the sneaker’s base color, as the bright crimson hue is applied liberally to both the mesh upper and midsole. Contrasting black accents appear on the tongue, collar and heel, the latter embellished with Nike Air branding for an OG-inspired touch.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Barrage Low White Black
adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange
sneakers.story: Kanye West brought together legendary designers Christian Tresser and Steven Smith for the adidas 700 MNVN. The sneaker's classic construction is ditched for an orange padded nylon upper complete with heat-welded overlays, a new heel tab and an oversized reflective '700' logo graphic across the lateral, omitting Three-Stripes branding. A black Boost-infused midsole is matched up with a herringbone rubber outsole. The 700 MNVN ‘Orange’ release was available only in select stores in two cities: Los Angeles and Paris.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Earth
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Earth' makes use of a Primeknit upper in a monochromatic dark khaki hue, complete with a post-dyed monofilament side strip for textural variety and a textile heel tab for easy on and off. The midsole ditches the traditional semi-translucent look for sidewalls in opaque tan rubber, concealing full-length Boost cushioning housed within. A gum rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot. The 'Earth' colorway is available only in North America and Latin America.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Flax
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Flax' dons a breathable Primeknit upper in an understated wheat hue, complemented by tonal rope laces and a post-dyed monofilament side stripe tinted in a muted yellow finish. The lightweight knit build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, partially visible beneath a semi-translucent rubber cage with ridged detailing. The 'Flax' colorway is available only in Asia Pacific, Africa, India and the Middle East.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Tail Light
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Tail Light' showcases a pop of bright orange at the stitched textile heel tab, along with a less concentrated shade of the same hue on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. The rest of the upper is constructed from light grey Primeknit in a minimalist one-piece build, complete with a distinctive center stitch running down the vamp. A semi-translucent rubber midsole houses adidas Boost cushioning for a smooth ride. The 'Tail Light' colorway is only available in Europe, Russia and Ukraine.

sneakers.name: Nike CruzrOne Black White
sneakers.story: The Nike CruzrOne ‘Black’ sits on a rocker-shaped rubber outsole, good for an exceptionally smooth heel-to-toe transition with each step. A Nike React foam midsole offers responsive cushioning, highlighted by a stacked heel and circular detailing that mimics the traction pattern found underfoot. Up top, the breathable black mesh build is reinforced with no-sew overlays and perforated midfoot cage. A wool lining on the low-cut collar offers a comfortable fit.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM (Lifestyle Model)
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Quantum 'Quantum' represents Kanye West’s debut sneaker in the basketball space. This lifestyle edition features a knit upper with wavy cut-out strips that reveal a breathable mesh base underneath. The grey and white tones used on both layers are complemented by reflective accents, an Off-White suede toe cap and solid black hits at the collar, tongue and heel. The mid-top is supported by a Boost midsole and a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Jordan 5 Retro Off-White Black
sneakers.story: The Off-White x Air Jordan 5 SP 'Muslin' delivers Virgil Abloh’s stylized take on the retro silhouette. The faded black textile upper blends traditional details, including a silver reflective tongue and embroidered Nike Air branding, with Virgil’s signature text on the laces and medial-side quarter panel. A pre-yellowed translucent rubber outsole adds to the sneaker’s vintage aesthetic.

sneakers.name: Xbox One x Air Jordan 3 Retro SE 'Unite' Special Box
adidas Y-3 Superskate Mid Off White
sneakers.story: The Y-3 Yohji Pro ‘White’ celebrates the 50th anniversary of the adidas Superstar by recrafting the iconic silhouette as a bulky high-top. The Off-White leather upper is accented with white leather three-stripes, a contrasting black heel tab and matching black on the suede eyestay. Yohji Yamamoto’s signature dominates the sneaker’s lateral side, extending from the upper to the midsole. A herringbone-tread rubber outsole offers durable traction underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Y-3 Superskate Low Off White
sneakers.story: On the occasion of its 50th anniversary, the Y-3 Yohji Pro Superstar Skate Low ‘White’ delivers a fashion-forward take on the adidas Superstar. The revamped design features a bulkier silhouette in an Off-White leather build, accented with white leather three-stripes, a black leather heel tab and synthetic suede eyestay in matching black. Y-3 branding adorns the padded tongue, while Yohji Yamamoto’s signature is scrawled on the sneaker’s lateral side

sneakers.name: Air Ship x Air Jordan 1 'New Beginnings'
sneakers.story: Released as one-half of the 'New Beginnings' Pack, the Nike Air Ship preceded the Air Jordan 1 as the silhouette that Michael Jordan wore at the start of his NBA career. The vintage high-top is clad in a white leather upper, accented with contrasting pops of Varsity Red at the padded collar and durable rubber outsole. The sneaker’s branding elements are similarly finished in crimson, including the leather Nike Swoosh and woven tongue tag.

sneakers.name: Jordan New Beginnings Pack Retro High 1 & Nike Air Ship
sneakers.story: The Air Ship PE x Air Jordan 1 'New Beginnings Pack' brings together the two silhouettes that kickstarted Michael Jordan’s partnership with Nike. Released in 1984, the Air Ship is the model that MJ wore at the start of his rookie season, before switching over to the Air Jordan 1 upon the sneaker’s release the following year. Both sneakers are finished in two-tone white and red colorways, with the Air Jordan 1 featuring a recrafted build that’s true to the high-top’s original 1985 form.

sneakers.name: Jordan 10 Retro Wings
sneakers.story: Releasing as part of Jordan Brand’s collection dedicated to promoting educational opportunities, the Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Wings' features a tumbled white leather upper with metallic silver mudguards, a green collar lining and multicolor piping. On the back, black stitched webbing runs down the length of the heel panel, embellished with round pops of color. The mid-top rides on an icy translucent rubber outsole, inscribed with MJ’s early career milestones.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Triple Black
sneakers.story: Kanye West tapped industry legends Christian Tresser and Steven Smith for the adidas 700 MNVN. The sneaker's usual mixed-material profile is overhauled in favor of triple-black nylon designed with heat-welded panels and an enlarged 3M '700' graphic along the lateral. This revamp adds a heel tab and drops the Three-Stripes emblem. The Boost-enclosed midsole is paired with a herringbone-patterned rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 'Black Cat'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 'Black Cat' draws direct inspiration from the namesake colorway of the Air Jordan 4, originally released in 2006 and inspired by one of Michael Jordan’s many nicknames. Like its antecedent, this pair features a monochromatic black finish throughout the exterior, save for subtle Electric Green accents on the herringbone rubber outsole. Additionally, reflective detailing throughout the upper shine bright during certain low-light conditions.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air Zoom 85 Runner Black White
sneakers.story: The Jordan Air Zoom 85 Runner 'Black' showcases Air Jordan 1-inspired design details on a lightweight running shoe built for a smooth ride. The all-black upper combines translucent textile with shiny synthetic patent leather on the forefoot overlay and heel, the latter featuring a debossed Jordan Wings logo. A contrasting white Cushlon midsole, housing forefoot Zoom Air cushioning, rides on a thin rubber outsole for lightweight traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Marsh
sneakers.story: A Yeezy Supply-exclusive colorway, Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Marsh' makes use of a breathable Primeknit upper in an understated shade of yellow. A darker mustard yellow is applied to the sneaker’s elastic collar, while the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe is rendered with light grey fibers. The semi-translucent rubber outsole is similarly tinted yellow and packs a full-length Boost unit for responsive cushioning.

sneakers.name: Nike SB Shane Black White
sneakers.story: The Nike Shane SB 'Black' showcases an essential color scheme on Shane O’Neill’s signature shoe. Outlined in white, a Nike Swoosh stands out against the low-top’s all-black upper, constructed from a blend of suede and canvas. Performance benefits include perforated ventilation at the toe, a foam sockliner with a Zoom Air unit in the heel, and a herringbone tread rubber outsole for superior board feel.

sneakers.name: New Balance 1700 Kith The Colorist Blue Toe
sneakers.story: Limited to just 1,700 pairs, the KITH x 1700K2 Made in USA 'Colorist' delivers a vibrant take on New Balance’s lifestyle runner. The all-suede upper combines a bright blue quarter panel with a slate toe box, yellow forefoot overlay, pink collar and purple heel. The latter features ‘Kith’ branding on the left shoe and ‘Fieg’ on the right. The layered construction up top is supported by a contrasting white midsole, complete with ABZORB cushioning for a smooth ride.

sneakers.name: New Balance 1700 Kith The Colorist Pink Toe
sneakers.story: Designed in collaboration with Ronnie Fieg, the Kith x 1700 Made in USA 'The Colorist - Pink Toe' is a limited release capped at 1,700 pairs. Split color blocking is used on the all-suede upper, mounted atop a contrasting white foam midsole with ABZORB cushioning at the forefoot and heel. Details include New Balance’s embroidered ‘N’ logo at the quarter panel and mismatched ‘Kith’ and ‘Fieg’ branding on the heel of the left and right shoe.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air Max 200 Super Bowl LIV
sneakers.story: The Jordan Air Max 200 XX 'Super Bowl LIV' celebrates the Big Game with vibrant hues that give the nod to the host city of Miami. The lifestyle silhouette features a leafy multicolor design on the tongue, heel and midfoot cage, the latter covered by a semi-translucent overlay. The rest of the upper is constructed from Off-White textile with canvas accents in green, coral and yellow. It all rides on a white foam midsole, fitted with a Max Air unit tinted in a bright red hue.

sneakers.name: Nike React Presto Undercover White
sneakers.story: The Undercover x React Presto 'White' is one of three monochromatic colorways drawn from a January 2020 collaboration between Nike and Jun Takahashi’s cult favorite brand. Inspired by the 2000 original, the sneaker features a white mesh upper with a speckled midfoot cage, revised lacing system and both leather and synthetic overlays at the forefoot. A plush React foam midsole gives way to a lug outsole for enhanced traction.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Non-Reflective)
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yeshaya' makes use of a re-engineered Primeknit upper that weaves in light grey fibers to contrast a neutral white base. A post-dyed monofilament side stripe adds a see-through element to the upper, while reflective threads in the rope laces add visibility in low-light conditions. The lightweight build sits atop a semi-translucent midsole housing adidas Boost cushioning.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective)
sneakers.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yeshaya Reflective' enhances the visual impact of the neutral two-tone Primeknit upper with reflective fibers woven into the build. Additional reflective hits appear on the rope laces and signature three-stripes that run down the interior of the rear collar, ultimately allowing the sneaker to shine in low-light conditions. A subtle yellow finish is applied to the semi-translucent rubber midsole, fitted with a Boost unit for lightweight cushioning.

sneakers.name: Jordan XXXIV Paris
sneakers.story: Limited to just 500 pairs, the NBA x Air Jordan 34 'Paris Game 2020' celebrates the first ever NBA game to be played in the French capital. The design is highlighted by swirling pink hues, visible beneath the transparent overlay that covers the majority of the upper, and unique details that include ‘PANAME’ lettering on the eyestay and ‘75’ on the heel of the right shoe. Additional pastel color hits appear on the midsole and Jumpman branding at the tongue.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air Max 200 Paris Saint Germain
sneakers.story: Launching in partnership with the French football club, the Paris Saint-Germain x Jordan Air Max 200 XX QS 'PSG' features mismatched red and blue accents on the upper of each shoe, built with a blend of mesh, suede and synthetic. Unique details include Paris branding on the lateral quarter panel and the PSG logo on the heel and sockliner. The mid-top rides on a black foam midsole, enhanced with a visible Air sole unit and supported underfoot by a translucent rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Type 02 OAMC Off-White
sneakers.story: Releasing in January 2020, the Type 02 'Off White' continues the creative partnership between adidas and OAMC that was originally kicked off the previous year. This hybrid silhouette combines a semi-translucent Supercourt RX midsole with a Stan Smith-inspired upper, constructed from full-grain leather in an Off-White finish. A herring-bone tread rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot.

sneakers.name: adidas Type O-2R OAMC Off-White
sneakers.story: The OAMC x adidas Type 0.2R sneaker brings together the clothing label's modern aesthetic and the German brand's tennis heritage. Launched in October 2019, this Off White version carries a vintage Stan Smith-inspired rubber upper with tonal metal eyelets and a branded tongue. The silhouette's name is printed on the counter. Its sculpted EVA midsole is taken from the Supercourt RX and rests atop a durable rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Type O-2L OAMC Off-White
sneakers.story: Designed in partnership with OAMC, the adidas Type 0.2L sneaker spins iconic design with bold, modern cues. This Off White iteration—delivered in October 2019—is styled with a vintage Stan Smith-inspired rubber upper, tonal lacing system and a signature heel badge. Co-branding and a logo graphic on the heel honor both brands. Atop a rubber outsole, the semi-transparent EVA midsole is a modern representation of Supercourt RX tooling.

sneakers.name: Solefly x Air Jordan 10 Retro Cleat 'Super Bowl' PE
sneakers.story: In honor of the Big Game, the Solefly x Air Jordan 10 Retro Cleat 'Super Bowl' PE was presented to a hand-selected group of top high school recruits from South Florida, all of whom were invited to participate in an exclusive flag football scrimmage. The performance football cleat features an Air Jordan 10 upper, constructed from white leather and mesh with contrasting pops of orange at the mudguard and heel, the latter featuring mismatched Solefly and Jumpman branding.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 'Unite'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 'Iridescent' is designed to shine on the hardwood, thanks to iridescent detailing on the eyestay and heel panel, the latter accented with mismatched multicolor pull loops and Nike Air logo hits. The rest of the all-white upper is constructed from semi-translucent mesh and synthetic, complete with similarly mismatched red and blue Flight branding on each tongue. The mid-top is anchored by a crisp white midsole and an icy translucent rubber midsole.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Unite'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 PF ‘Unite’ shows off an iridescent finish on the eyestay and heel panel, featuring mismatched Nike Air branding between the left and right shoe. The rest of the upper is built with white synthetic leather and translucent textile, supported by a midsole that combines an Eclipse Plate with visible Zoom Air for extra-responsive cushioning. A herringbone-tread rubber outsole delivers superior traction underfoot.

sneakers.name: Nike React Infinity Run Black White
sneakers.story: The React Infinity Run 'Black' applies a simple color scheme to a performance runner engineered to go the distance. In addition to an upper that uses revised Flyknit made with three discreet layers for added strength and durability, the React foam midsole is fortified with a higher stack height and wider stance for a more stable ride. A high-traction rubber outsole provides sure footing through each stride.

sneakers.name: Nike SB Alleyoop Black White
sneakers.story: The Nike SB Alleyoop 'Black White' features an essential color scheme on a low-profile skate shoe. The upper is constructed from black mesh with matching suede overlays at the toe and heel. Contrasting white hits appear on the sneaker’s various branding elements, including the Swoosh, Nike tongue tag and SB-branded heel tab. Underfoot, a circular tread pattern on the rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

sneakers.name: Jordan Air Max 200 White Challenge Red Black
Jordan Air Max 200 Fire Red
sneakers.story: The Jordan Air Max 200 'Fire Red' combines a large-volume Air sole unit with a lifestyle basketball shoe that borrows elements from the Air Jordan 4. The upper, finished in monochromatic Fire Red, combines ripstop nylon with synthetic suede overlays and a perforated semi-translucent quarter panel. Finished with Nike Air branding at the heel, the low-top rides on a speckled Off-White midsole housing a Max 200 Air unit.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Chinese New Year'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan 34 PF ‘Chinese New Year’ rings in the Year of the Rat with a Chinese coin-inspired design on the sneaker’s translucent textile paneling. The rest of the upper, constructed from a blend of leather, synthetic and mesh, maintains a neutral white and black color scheme, with contrasting pops of Digital Pink on the webbing heel tabs. It all rides on a lightweight foam midsole that combines an Eclipse plate with Zoom Air cushioning.

sneakers.name: adidas POD S3-2 Off White Hi Res Yellow
New Balance 990v2 Kith Shark
sneakers.story: NYC brand, KITH partnered with New Balance to launch the KITH x 990v2 'Shark,' a September 2019 update to the 1982 streetwear staple. A pebbled leather tongue joins nubuck and leather on the upper to create a multi-layered composition, adding structure to the silhouette. For a patriotic vibe, 'USA' is embroidered on the heel and is congruent with New Balance branding on the tongue. An ABZORB midfoot and ENCAP midsole sit atop a full-foot rubber outsole to deliver unrelenting cushion underfoot.

sneakers.name: KITH x 998 'Shark'
sneakers.story: Kith founder and sneaker designer, Ronnie Fieg collaborated with New Balance to launch the KITH x 998 'Shark' streetwear shoe in September 2019. Building upon the iconic style of the OG 998, the contemporary version is outfitted with a mesh upper encapsulated by pigskin suede and leather overlays for structure. An ABZORB rubber midsole encourages energy responsiveness down below for comfort with each step. Recognizing the brand, an 'NB' logo accents the heel and a double 'N' logo his the sidewall.

sneakers.name: KITH x 990v2 'Shark'
sneakers.story: NYC brand, KITH partnered with New Balance to launch the KITH x 990v2 'Shark,' a September 2019 update to the 1982 streetwear staple. A pebbled leather tongue joins nubuck and leather on the upper to create a multi-layered composition, adding structure to the silhouette. For a patriotic vibe, 'USA' is embroidered on the heel and is congruent with New Balance branding on the tongue. An ABZORB midfoot and ENCAP midsole sit atop a full-foot rubber outsole to deliver unrelenting cushion underfoot.

sneakers.name: New Balance 997S Fusion Kith x United Arrows and Sons Grey Pink
sneakers.story: Drawn from a larger three-piece footwear collection, KITH x United Arrows & Sons x 997S Fusion features a distinctive colorway inspired by a 2009 New Balance collaboration with United Arrows. The shoe combines the traditional upper of the 997 with the revised tooling of the 997S, with a neutral grey and black color scheme that’s accented with a pop of pink on the signature ‘N’ logo.

sneakers.name: New Balance 997S Fusion Kith x nonnative Brown Beige
sneakers.story: The KITH x nonnative x 997S Fusion ‘Dune’ brings together three creative partners on a hybrid silhouette, one inspired by the New Balance 997.5 ‘Dune’ collaboration with nonnative from 2011. Built with a combination of mesh and pigskin suede, the shoe is finished with a triple-stacked ‘N’ logo, a nod to New Balance’s three partner brands.

sneakers.name: New Balance 997 OG Kith United Arrows and Sons
sneakers.story: The Kith x United Arrows & Sons x New Balance collaboration references one of Ronnie Fieg’s favorite NB silhouettes: the 997.5. Staying true to the aesthetic of the OG 997 shape, the shoe updates the construction with premium textiles, including soft suede and mesh paneling. The mostly grey upper is contrasted with vibrant shades of pink and purple, while a yellowed application emerges on the ENCAP midsole for a retro look.

sneakers.name: New Balance 997S Kith United Arrows and Sons
sneakers.story: The KITH x United Arrows & Sons x 997S released in November 2018 as a three-party collaboration inspired by one of Ronnie Fieg’s favorite New Balance releases: the United Arrows 997.5 from 2009. Modernized with a neoprene tongue, this special-edition 997S features a neutral grey upper in mesh and suede, accented with a triple-stacked ‘N’ logo on the quarter panel.

sneakers.name: New Balance 997 OG Kith nonnative
sneakers.story: Kith partnered with New Balance and Japanese retailer nonnative for an exclusive capsule that celebrates one of Ronnie Fieg’s favorite NB styles ever made: the 997.5. This iteration borrows design details from the original and places them onto the 997 silhouette while keeping the general tan and Cobalt Blue color palette intact. The runner revamps the typical mesh and suede formation by adding pony hair applications on the tongue, heel and ‘N’ branding. The three different colors on the saddle pay homage to the three partners involved in the collaborative project.

sneakers.name: New Balance 997S Kith nonnative
sneakers.story: The KITH x nonnative x 997S ‘Dune’ is one of three New Balance collaborations that released in November 2018. Taking inspiration from the 997.5 ‘Dune,’ launched jointly by New Balance and nonnative in 2011, this pair features a mesh and suede upper in varying shades of tan. Contrasting pops of metallic silver and blue are used on the unique triple-stacked ‘N’ logo.

sneakers.name: New Balance 993 Kith Black (Standard Width)
sneakers.story: Originally unveiled to the world in 2008, the New Balance 993 combines features from its 991 and 992 predecessors while introducing technical improvements. The upper sports a breathable mesh base with pigskin leather overlays built to enhance the structure of the silhouette and resist abrasion from the elements. Down below, the ABZORB DTS midsole is a Dynamic Transitioning System featuring cushion and stability for shock absorption. A tough rubber outsole helps to add on the miles.

sneakers.name: New Balance 990v4 Kith Navy
sneakers.story: An updated version of the classic 990, the 990v4 'Navy White' sneaker sports a monochromatic suede and mesh upper underscored with reflective silver accents, 990 branding and its signature ‘N’ logo. First introduced in 1998, the ABZORB cushioning technology in its midsole provides shock absorption and displaces energy for optimal impact control. Its finished off with a high-wearing NDurance rubber outsole.

sneakers.name: New Balance 990v3 Kith Navy
sneakers.story: The New Balance 990 was originally released in 1982 with the plan to develop the best running sneaker no matter how much time it took or money it cost. Re-launched in 2012, the 990v3 'Navy White’ replicates the classic design with updated elements. A premium upper features mesh underlays and reflective details for enhanced visibility. Below, an ABZORB midsole with ENCAP technology and a treaded rubber outsole help provide support and traction.

sneakers.name: Jordan Eclipse Chukka 'Black'
sneakers.story: Building off of Nike Roshe, the Jordan Eclipse Chukka draws from a series of sources, including the classic Chukka boot that dates back to the traditional footwear of the British army. The Jordan Eclipse Chukka features a black woven textile upper with a braided pattern and a neoprene throat for an adaptive fit. The sneaker also sports Air technology in the midsole for lightweight cushioning and a branded heel with the Jumpman logo in Dark Grey.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High NYC '23NY' Sample
Jordan Flight Origin 3 'Black'
sneakers.story: Boasting various modified Air Jordan design details, the Jordan Flight Origin blends old school style with contemporary construction. Nike’s Jordan Flight Origin 3 'Black' sneaker expands upon the franchise featuring an allover tonal colorway, accented with printed laces and contrast Jumpman logos on the tongue and heel. Underfoot, the shoe is supported with lightweight cushioning and a durable treaded outsole.

sneakers.name: CP3.X 'Space Jam'
sneakers.story: This CP3.X 'Space Jam' draws inspiration from the original release of the Air Jordan 11 Space Jam. The sneaker features a black Flywire upper accented with Concord hits and white speckling. The low-top also sports a full-length Air unit, a TPU cage on the side panels and a solid rubber outsole. The celestial design on the side panels serves as a nod to the zodiac signs of Paul’s family.

sneakers.name: Jordan True Flight 'Black'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan True Flight offers a new spin on the Air Jordan 7, featuring a lighter composition and a full-length Air unit. The retro-inspired design also includes a herringbone outsole and a neoprene Dynamic Fit sleeve. This simple black and white colorway sports a metallic gold Jumpman at the ankle.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid 'Ice Blue'
sneakers.story: Released during the 2017 NCAA Tournament, the ‘Ice Blue’ edition of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid gives off University of North Carolina vibes. The Varsity Royal upper combines with Ice Blue on the toe box, heel and Swoosh to complete a colorway similar to Michael Jordan’s college alma mater. Varsity Royal also appears on the ‘Wings’ logo, Jumpman on the heel and outsole, while a white midsole provides a crisp contrast.

sneakers.name: Air Jordan 6 'First Championship'
sneakers.story: This Air Jordan 6 is inspired by goalkeeper Tim Howard and celebrates the US Men’s National Soccer team. The shoe features a white leather base that is covered in 3M reflective material, complemented with speckled navy midsole accents and translucent touches on the tongue, heel, and outsole. The shoe itself never officially hit the market and there is expected to only be around 30 pairs floating around amongst the general public.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Light Brown Gum (Chocolate)
sneakers.story: First seen during Kanye’s Yeezy Season 2 presentation at New York Fashion Week, the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘Chocolate’ sneaker was officially released a month later on October 15, 2016. The design combines a light brown nubuck upper with an elasticated mid-foot strap, perforated vamp, and a gum Boost midsole that glows in the dark. The sneaker also features an upgraded YKK ankle zipper.

sneakers.name: Jordan True Flight
sneakers.story: Cool Grey, a popular color on heritage Jordan offerings, makes its way onto the Jordan True Flight. Constructed with nubuck paneling on the majority of the upper, the shoe is equipped with a mesh tongue for enhanced breathability, while the design itself borrows inspiration from the Jordan 7’s aesthetic. The white outsole contrasts the look.

sneakers.name: Jordan Eclipse 'Cool Grey'
sneakers.story: Made for off-court wear, the Jordan Eclipse features a minimalist soft knit upper in heathered grey. Embellishments are limited to an extended fabric tongue loop and Jumpman branding on the heel panel. The lightweight build up top is mounted on a contrasting white cupsole, equipped with an Air Sole unit at the heel and a herringbone traction outsole pattern for multidirectional traction.

sneakers.name: Jordan True Flight 'Black'
sneakers.story: Taking inspiration from the iconic design of the Air Jordan 7, the Jordan True Flight updates the heritage basketball sneaker with a lifestyle appeal, featuring a Triple Black color scheme and nubuck paneling throughout the upper construction. Resting on an Air Sole unit for cushioning, the shoe also utilizes a herringbone pattern on the outsole for traction.

sneakers.name: Laika x Air Jordan 15 Retro 'Kubo and the Two Strings'
Jordan Eclipse 'White Infrared'
sneakers.story: A lifestyle silhouette, the Jordan Eclipse takes on a straightforward two-tone colorway on its breathable mesh upper. The shoe’s tongue, vamp and laces are finished in bright Infrared 23, while the overlay that wraps around the quarter panel and heel is rendered in contrasting white. A gold Jumpman adorns the heel, and a speckled midsole packs an encapsulated Air Sole unit for a cushioned ride.

sneakers.name: Jordan Academy 'Infrared'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan Academy 'Infrared' sneaker adds a futuristic feel to the Jordan Brand lineup. The shoe’s unique, textured upper is constructed from a lightweight textile fabrication, with a supportive ankle strap and convenient stretch-gore laces for easy on-off access. Flexible cushioning is provided through the injected Air-Sole unit, while a non-marking rubber outsole with a strategic pattern underfoot helps with traction.

sneakers.name: Jordan Hydro 5 Retro Slide 'White Metallic Gold'
Jordan Reveal 'Metallic Gold Coin'
sneakers.story: The Jordan Reveal brings minimalist style to an off-court silhouette supported with Nike Air cushioning. The streamlined design is accentuated with a clean white colorway, executed on a breathable mesh upper with a tonal white leather overlay that wraps around the heel. The pristine finish is accented with metallic gold Jumpman logos and matching gold speckling on the midsole.

sneakers.name: Jordan Trainer ST 'University Blue'
sneakers.story: Jordan expands upon their training-specific footwear offerings with the Trainer ST, which is rendered in a University Blue and Midnight Navy color scheme that’s contrasted with Infrared 23 accents on the Jumpman logo and outsole. The upper is constructed with a breathable mesh knit on the toe and tongue, while the iconic cement print is woven into the design for a heritage look. The midsole features FlightFlex technology.

sneakers.name: Jordan Trainer 1 Low 'Anthracite'
sneakers.story: The Jordan Trainer 1 Low features a black elephant print jacquard pattern with a contrasting silver Jumpman logo on the side wall. The sneaker also boasts a low cut neoprene bootie for wider range of motion and a contrasting white midsole for responsive cushioning.

sneakers.name: Jordan Ultra Fly
sneakers.story: The Jordan Ultra Fly sports an engineered mesh upper with Kurim cage-like overlays across the upper. The low top also sports Hyper Turquoise accents on the 9-chamber Zoom Air unit and inner sleeve. An oversized reflective silver Jumpman logo takes over the medial heel, completing the look.

sneakers.name: Jordan Horizon 'Gym Red'
sneakers.story: The Air Jordan Horizon ‘Gym Red’ takes evident influence from the design of the Jordan 13, featuring a seamless Gym Red upper formation that’s blanketed with a honeycomb netting to break up the tonal appearance. An asymmetrical lacing system provides added stability, while the midsole and outsole sport contrasting black.

sneakers.name: Jordan Melo M12 'Dungeon'
sneakers.story: Jordan Brand’s signature shoe for player Carmelo Anthony gets its twelfth release with the M12. The basketball sneaker comes with a flexible mesh upper and asymmetrical loop lacing system. The sole incorporates two Zoom Air units for cushioning and FlightSpeed technology for a responsive energy return.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Oxford Tan
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Oxford Tan’ features an oxford/light stone Primeknit upper with tonal oxford laces, suede patches on the medial sides, and a tan Boost outsole. First worn by Kanye at the August 2015 MTV VMAs, the fourth colorway of the Yeezy 350 was released at select adidas Originals Retail stores on December 29th, 2015.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black
sneakers.story: Kanye teased the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘Black’ colorway in a February 2015 interview with New York’s Power 105.1 FM. Later he was spotted wearing a black suede/gum sole iteration of the sneaker at a Givenchy show during New York Fashion Week. Released on December 19, 2015, as the second colorway of the Yeezy Boost 750 line, the ‘Black’ sneaker features a full suede upper, perforated vamp, and ankle zipper.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock
sneakers.story: Following the ‘Turtle Dove’ and ‘Pirate’ colorways, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Moonrock’ features a moonrock/agate grey Primeknit upper and a moonrock Boost outsole. First previewed on Instagram by Kim Kardashian and released on November 14th, 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Moon Rock’ was sold exclusively at stores that carried Yeezy Season One apparel.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Pirate Black
sneakers.story: The adidas Yeezy 950 Boot is a triple fusion of three classic silhouettes. Unveiled in October 2015, this 'Pirate' edition mirrors a combat and duck boot with a nylon and textile upper and weatherized laces. A rear pull tab aids entrance, while a debossed tongue label authenticates the look. Elevated by a high-profile midsole, the aggressive, hiking-inspired tread designates the style for sartorial performance.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Moonrock
sneakers.story: The Yeezy 950 Boot 'Moonrock' features a textile upper dressed in a Moonrock color scheme with suede accents on the eyestay and tonal metal eyelets. The sneaker also sports a rounded toe for added comfort, a topstitched vamp, padded lining for a snug fit, and a heavy-duty rubber lug sole for impact protection and superior grip.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Peyote
sneakers.story: The Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Peyote’ was one of the four original colorways of the duck boot-military boot hybrid that launched as part of Kanye West’s Yeezy Season 1 range. The light tan hue is tonally consistent with the color story of the collection at large, which is highlighted by a dark and muddy palette. The rugged build makes use of a combination of ballistic mesh, suede and durable throughout the upper, while the outsole makes use of a high-traction rubber tread.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Chocolate
sneakers.story: Released in October 2015 as part of Yeezy Season 1, the Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Chocolate’ features a silhouette that combines a duck boot with a military boot, wrapped up in a monochromatic build. The materials include rubber, ballistic mesh, and suede, all finished in the same dark brown palette. Exterior branding is limited to adidas and Yeezy wordmarks on the outsole, as well as the mismatched tongue tags.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2015)
sneakers.story: Released on August 22nd, 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Pirate Black’ features a pirate black/dark gray Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned dark grey rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove
sneakers.story: First seen on Kanye and his models at the Yeezy Season 1 fashion show in February 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Turtle Dove’ was the second shoe released in the adidas Yeezy collection after the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘OG.’ Dropped on June 27, 2015, the ‘Turtle Dove’ sold out instantly online and was eventually anointed 2015’s Shoe of the Year at the Footwear News 29th Annual Achievement Awards.

sneakers.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 OG Light Brown
sneakers.story: Kanye West’s very first collaborative adidas shoe, the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘OG’ released worldwide February 2017 in extremely limited quantities. The towering boot-like builds showcases a radical departure from West’s previous designs, featuring a light brown all-suede upper mounted atop a partially ribbed, Boost-equipped rubber tooling in a subtle Off-White shade. The minimalist design is accented with oversized rope laces, perforated detailing on the toe box, and a wide midfoot strap in a tonal twill fabrication. A hidden zipper on the lateral side provides easy on and off.

sneakers.name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg x Nice Kicks 1.0
sneakers.story: Limited to only 250 pairs, this 2009 collaboration between online sneaker magazine Nice Kicks and ASICS was part of the Trilogy Project curated by Ronnie Fieg for New York City footwear retailer David Z. The Nice Kicks x Gel Lyte 3 'Trilogy Project’ sports a bright red upper with grey and white accents. The runner is also distinguished by its unique blend of materials, combining perforated pig skin suede on the toe box and side panels with a nubuck toe cap, ballistic mesh on the tongue and ankle and 3M reflective patent leather accents.

sneakers.name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg Culture Shoq 1.0
Louis Vuitton Mr. Hudson Kanye White
sneakers.story: The Kanye West x Louis Vuitton sneaker collection dropped in July 2009 with three different models and ten different colorways. The Mr. Hudson, named after the English musician who signed with Kanye’s GOOD Music label in 2008, is reminiscent of a tasseled boat shoe. This ‘White’ model boasts a monochromatic look, with a quilted pull-flap on the heel and embossed Louis Vuitton flower motifs on the midsole. Only the gold bands on the tassels provide color.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Blink
sneakers.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Blink’ from April 2009 is one of three sneakers that kicked off Kanye West’s partnership with Nike. The high-top blends a variety of materials and textures on the upper, finished in tonal black with a pop of bright pink on the lining, lace lock, and ‘Yeezy’ print on the heel loop. While the vamp features smooth suede construction, the midfoot strap and heel panel are covered in an all-over ‘Y’ print for an eye-catching texture.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Zen Grey
sneakers.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Zen’ launched in April 2009, one of three colorways that made up the first collaborative release from Kanye West and Nike. An overall new silhouette with details borrowed from the Nike archives, the design employs a mostly neutral colorway with vibrantly hued accents throughout. The patent leather midfoot strap comes in a unique texture while the toe cap features premium suede. Underfoot, the nondescript rubber outsole glows green when the lights go down.

sneakers.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Net Tan
sneakers.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Net’ launched in June 2009 and would be the third and final colorway of the debut sneaker from Kanye West and Nike to hit stores. The shoe features a beige leather upper stopping at a high collar lined in pink, mounted on a two-tone midsole borrowed from the Nike Air Jordan 3. The smooth and glossy finish on the patent leather midfoot strap is contrasted by a perforated leather vamp and suede toe wrap, embossed with an all-over ‘Y’ print.
